cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper deals with natural language processing and parsing spoken utterances, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper also focuses on acoustic-prosodic features, which are related to sound and speech processing. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The study of conversational speech and disfluencies can be related to social interactions and communication networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses convolutional and recurrent neural networks for modeling and integrating lexical and acoustic-prosodic information. 
- cs.SD (Signal Processing): The paper deals with processing and analyzing speech signals, which is related to signal processing.
